National Security Advisor Susan E. Rice met with Shotaro Yachi, Secretary General of Japan's National Security Secretariat. They discussed various security issues, including North Korea's nuclear and missile programs and maritime security in East Asia. They also talked about the progress in revising the Guidelines for U.S.-Japan Defense Cooperation, which will help the Alliance respond to modern security challenges. Rice emphasized the importance of strong relations between Japan and South Korea and the need for G-7 unity in responding to Russian aggression in Ukraine.